<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1931-11-05T09:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1931-11-05T09:00:00-05:00" n="165" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d165">
                                <note rend="inline" type="source">462.00R296/5287: Telegram</note>
                                <head><hi rend="italic">The Minister in Greece</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Skinner</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                                            State</gloss></hi></head>
                                <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Athens</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1931-11-05T16:00:00+02:00">November 5, 1931—4
                                            p.m.</date><lb/>[Received November 5—1:20
                                        p.m.]</dateline></opener>
                                <p>50. The International Financial Commission informs me that in
                                    consequence of information received from the Greek Government,
                                    it regards itself as authorized to suspend payment of amounts
                                    due <pb facs="0328" n="214" xml:id="pg_214"/> the United States
                                    on November 10, 1931 and May 10, 1932 in consequence of the
                                    applicability of the President’s moratorium program.</p>
                                <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Skinner</hi></signed></closer>
                            </div>
                            </body></text></TEI>